# Angular Development Guidelines

- Use standalone components by default; avoid NgModules unless legacy integration requires otherwise.
- Keep components single-purpose: UI rendering + lightweight orchestration only.
- Prefer signals for local state and derived data with `computed()`; avoid imperative mutable shared state.
- Use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` on every component.
- Prefer `inject()` in services and `input()` / `output()` for inputs and outputs.
- Use route-based lazy loading for feature modules.
- Keep templates declarative with Angular control flow (`@if`, `@for`, `@switch`).
- For template conditionals, keep expressions simple and move logic to component computed values.

```ts
// ❌ Avoid
let data = signal<any>([]);

// ✅ Prefer
const items = signal<readonly Item[]>([]);
const filteredItems = computed(() => items().filter((item) => item.active));
```
